column1: #Text=Edinburgh 's ' Million Mask March ' flies distinctly Scottish colours
#Text=Amongst other Guy Fawkes Night partying , the now-regular march to the Scottish Parliament by Anonymous saw significantly higher attendance , Wednesday , at this year 's event .
#Text=With Catalan flags and pro-Independence Saltires flying , activist numbers had clearly been swelled by the referendum result .

#Text=Regardless of chanting , which included taunts over the lack of BBC presence , marchers were in good spirits .
#Text=The crowd outside the Scottish Parliament was a wide mix of ages .
#Text=Not all who took part wore Guy Fawkes masks .
#Text=Most of the crowd were well wrapped-up to guard against the night air chill .
#Text=Pro- Catalan independence flag flying as part of the protest at the Scottish Parliament .
#Text=Police Scotland were conspicuous amongst the crowd , although not present in large numbers .

#Text=Some protesters self-identified as part of the 45 % of the Scottish electorate who voted Yes to Independence .
#Text=Independence sentiment was highly-visible amongst protesters at the Scottish Parliament .
